
 1. Go to link [Skip this drive] and then get a command prompt.when bitlocker drive key appears 

go to cmd
manage-bde -status c:
3. If the status is “locked”, use this command and end with the recovery key to unlock:
manage-bde -unlock c: -rp <your 48-digit recovery password>
4. After that, use this command to suspend protection:
manage-bde -protectors -disable c:
5. Finally, exit the program and reboot the computer.
